<br>
<br>
Okay, lets say we use common sense to generate a list of 50 rules that cover everything that we can possibly think of that is not acceptable.<br>
<br>
The people we really need the rules for, are the ones who won't listen to those rules in the first place.<br>
<br>
So, we only need those rules for our own benefit, to make sure people know why we do stuff so they don't think we are nazi's, and to make sure people don't accidently break the rules.<br>
<br>
First of all, people will think we are Nazi's with or without rules, so that point is relativley irrelevant, showing reasons behind a common sense decision is more important than the rules, because it would stop me taking some bizaare rule and twisting it for my own personal interperation.<br>
<br>
Second of all, people will keep on accidently breaking the rules, because if we have fifty, they won't bother to read them all. Plain and simple.<br>
<br>
Best we can do, is a polite warning that something has been said that breaks a rule.<br>
<br>
<br>
Third of all, all rules will probably be open for interperation to apply to many things. Now, If you write a list of 20 rules along those line, I can twist their interperation to fit every single post anyone on this board has made ever.<br>
<br>
And that is pissing people off unnecessarily.<br>
<br>
<br>
Best scenario is you have the three basic rules. No spam. No Porn. No RL threats. And Explain how moderators will make a big decision.<br>
<br>
This is doing the EXACT same thing as creating a list of rules but...<br>
<br>
A) We don't have to think more up as the need arises<br>
B) We don't have idiots complaining that we aren't upholding Rule #1512<br>
C) We can still show how we aren't being Nazi's by explaining ourselves<br>
<br>
<br>
Seriously Wrin, the number of times we actually need to USE a rule to do something pales into comparrison to the number of times you bitch about a rule being used, or not used. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://216.94.170.106/phpBB2/images/avatars/19834029863f67d57cdd2ec.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
