Anything that is of the form<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>I WILL</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> [do something really bad to you IRL]<br>
<br>
Is not acceptable<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>I SHOULD</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> [do something really bad to you IRL]<br>
<br>
Is acceptable<br>
<br>
or, as an example :<br>
Damn you kwip, I am going to come round and beat your head IRL<br>
<br>
Is not acceptable.<br>
<br>
Damn you kwip, I should go round and beat your head IRL<br>
<br>
Is acceptable.<br>
<br>
<br>
I didn't write this particular rule to be honest, but because as you say there are fine line between what constitutes a threat and what constitutes not threat, this eradicates that line by making it neccesary to change the wording so it always sounds 'more of an idle threat'.<br>
<br>
Of course, this may well change in the near future should we all decide to do away with it.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
